  "description": [
    "THE BENGAL HURKARU of more than three years have been delivered from it will be one of the finest days of my life and my French heart has enjoyed no less the end of their distresses than the li beration of the country The provinces which have so painfully occupied my thoughts till this day deserveto fix those of the nation which has admired as I have done their heroic resignation BENGAL HURKARU CALCUTTA Accounts from Lisbon stated that the King of Portugal had expressed his fixed determination to remain in the Brazils during the remainder of his reign Addresses of Condolence to the Prince Regent jon the death of the Queen had been generally presented from the corporations in England and Scotland The Earl of Aberdeen had received the Prince Regents permission to use the name of Hamilton in addition to that of Gordon as a memorial of respect for the memory of his late fatherinlaw the Marquis of Abercorn THURSDAY JUNE 3 1819 The noble unanimity of heart and of sentiments which you manifested when I called upon you for the means to fulfilonr engagements wasa brilliant proof of the attach ment of the French to their country"
